##I don't know how much longer I can hold on | story FM

Story

Features, welcome to the story FM. Here, we tell your story with your voice. Every Monday, Wednesday and Friday, all platforms are updated simultaneously.

Click on the picture above to jump to the "story FM" applet and listen to the real person. Remember to add "my little program" , one-click to listen to the whole story Yo!

The story we're focusing on today is not about the epidemic, but about a group of people who have been seriously affected by it.

On Weibo, there is a topic called non-pneumonia people seeking help, which is updated every day and has been read more than 40 million times. Those seeking help were mostly cancer patients and their families who had been diagnosed or started chemotherapy before the outbreak. But after the outbreak, their treatment has been put on hold, and there is no end in sight to when it will be restored.

As more and more new patients are being treated and discharged from hospitals, we have produced this special program to draw your attention to the situation of cancer patients in Wuhan, Hubei and even the whole country.

Nom, NASOPHARYNGEAL cancer

-1-

Chemotherapy that can't wait

I'm a NASOPHARYNGEAL cancer patient. Last November, I began treatment at the Wuhan Union Hospital's Cancer Center with three rounds of induction chemotherapy followed by thirty-three rounds of radiation and two rounds of concurrent chemotherapy.

This year, January 10, I finished the Third Induction Chemotherapy, the hospital let me go home to rest, about the fourth day of the Lunar New Year to do radiation therapy.

When the city was sealed off, I called the hospital to see what to do. The doctor also did not think that the epidemic would develop so quickly, and answered that it is difficult to say anything now, let me wait at home phone, after attending doctors will contact me.

The first time I received a call from the hospital was before the Ninth Day of the ninth lunar month. The doctor said we might have to wait a few days for radiation because of the outbreak. The second call is the ninth day, he said the epidemic is very serious now, if you come over, to think clearly. Cancer patients belong to a special group, low immunity, easy to infection. He advised me to wait until after the Fifteenth Day of the first lunar month, when things might be better.

I had no choice but to wait at home.

But not long after, I heard that the Cancer Center at Concorde had been requisitioned. The doctor called me and said, now can not come over, you wait at home first, we try to tell the hospital leadership feedback, for the early resumption of normal services.

I asked. When would that be? He said he couldn't give you a definite time, so take some medicine if you have to. I asked if the pills worked, and he said it was better than nothing.

It's a prescription drug called Capecitabine, and they don't prescribe it unless you're in their hospital. At that time, Hubei is not allowed to go out, I would like to do a friend to help buy a few boxes, but now this medicine only two boxes.

■ A medicine box photographed by Xiaonuo

Now, I have been off treatment for a month and a half, I do not know whether the body's cancer cells are very honest or very active, because we can not do tests so do not know. If we wait any longer, it's only gonNA get worse. We really don't know what tomorrow will bring.

-2-

The feedback you can't wait for

After the cancer center closed, I and the hospital with two layers of patients to pull a wechat group, there are more than 40 people, everyone in the group to discuss ideas every day.

We first reported the situation to the Wuhan Mayor Hotline, called several times, all said they have reported the problem to the higher level, let us wait for the notice. We also made a call to Wuhan Health Commission, they said to record the situation, is also waiting for notice.

Health Commission also gave me an idea: you go to consult the Union Hospital leadership, see how the leadership response. And then he gave me a land line from Concorde Hospital, the number of the duty officer. The duty leader listened to very sympathetically, he said that will report the situation with the courtyard leader, strives for the early solution, lets me maintain the telephone unblocked at any time.

But all the feedback has gone unanswered.

■ A hospital message forwarded to Xiao Nuo by a patient on Feb. 12

My home is in a county-level city, away from Wuhan more than 100 kilometers, drive an hour and a half can arrive. Our local hospital doesn't accept chemotherapy. Here is a small place, radiation therapy does not have equipment, the only unit that can be chemotherapy is the people's Hospital.

But now, the oncology department there has also been abolished, all merged into the fever department, all to treat pneumonia patients.

We also consulted the National Sun Yat-sen University in Guangzhou, but they wouldn't let us in; the Shanghai Cancer Hospital wouldn't let us in, because people like me wouldn't let us in. Even if we go in, we'll be in quarantine for 14 days. And I don't know if they're gonNA take patients like us, because we're already halfway there, and the treatment's all coming together.

Here we now stop all the provincial approval procedures, that is, all the provincial are not allowed to do. Even if can go out, now encounter Hubei Native are not let down the highway, directly persuade back.

Now I have been staying at home did not go out, also dare not go out, our resistance is too weak, go out very easy to be infected. These two days, our side of the measures have been upgraded, to fight a 14-day blockade, the city closed, all the district is closed, the corridor is closed, not allowed to come out, so do not talk about going out.

I can not sleep at night now, anxious everyday, easy insomnia. Every day I was Random Thoughts, terrified that I wouldn't see tomorrow. The feeling is, in plain English, to die at home. Sitting in front of the window, facing the open road, waiting for life slowly exhausted.

The rest of the time is spent staring at the news on your phone, checking to see if you have any news or good ideas from the group. All the inmates are like me. They're all over the place. No response.

We didn't really have a problem requisitioning the hospital during the outbreak. We're not trying to force the government to evict people who are in critical condition. They're lives. Our appeal is very simple, is that the government can find a way to give us a life path. For example, there are many private hospitals in Putian, why not expropriate them, but take up the resources of our special patients?

Vivian, father has lung Adenocarcinoma

Forced to discontinue treatment

My father was diagnosed late last year with lung Adenocarcinoma and brain metastases. His disease is being treated with chemotherapy and k-drug immunotherapy every three weeks while still being treated, theoretically for two years.

Diagnosis from family members

As I recall, it was technically January 28th, and my father was due for his third treatment. At that time, the doctor told us that the Fourth Day Card in the hospital rest time, so we were informed a little later two days, seventh day to go through the admission procedures.

On the sixth day, I asked the head nurse on our floor: Can we go to the hospital tomorrow? As a result, the head nurse advised me not to come. She said that there were patients infected with new pneumonia on the ground floor of the hospital, and there were also infected medical staff. They're cleaning up. I'll be in touch in seven or eight days. But the hospital wasn't closed at the time. There were old patients there.

On February 5th or 6th, when I contacted again, I found that there were about 24 floors in the radiation and chemotherapy section of the central South Hospital, called Foshan -- almost all of them closed, leaving only two or three floors for the elderly patients, a patient who's just about to die. And they're all in isolation, so I don't know if those people have NCP.

In a week, when I went back to the attending doctor, he told me that the hospital might be called into fever clinic and that no new patients would be admitted. And when I asked again the other day, I said I had cleared out all the old patients, and the whole department was closed.

They advised me to look for a small hospital near you and get the medicine out first. It's kind of pushing us out, and I think they're under a lot of pressure.

■ screenshot of a conversation between Vivian and the doctor

Missed a referral

In fact, I heard about pneumonia as early as December 30 last year. My husband did not know is in the friend circle or in the group to see a screen shot, is the Wuhan Municipal Commission of Health Construction screen shot, said to check (pneumonia) this matter, also stamped with a red seal.

My husband told me that you should be careful, wear a mask when you go out, and don't go in crowded places. Then my brother saw the news in Wuhan, China, that SARS had started.

But then the government came out and said No. Then ten thousand family banquets and meetings were held as usual. So I didn't care too much, just bought some masks, alcohol and the like online.

If the rumors hadn't been dispelled, I would have believed the pneumonia story and would have been ready to refer my father to a doctor or go away for treatment. Another reason not to move was because I was afraid of too much trouble, because my father had been found brain metastases tumor, had an operation, did not dare to move him.

I know a pharmaceutical rep for K-pharmaceuticals who knows every oncology department in Wuhan. I asked him to understand all the larger hospitals in the three towns of Wuhan, including Tongji, Xiehe and the provincial cancer hospital. He said that none of the hospitals are accepting new patients at present, and they are all going to be quarantined under the same administrative order.

I was thinking this morning, if we're GONNA do a transfer, should we just call the hospital and check in. But I didn't know how to get in touch, and now it's not just Wuhan, it's the neighborhood.

So I really don't know what to do now. If we keep this up, which I hate to say, we're GONNA die at home.

Compared to my father, my mother is slightly less ill. She has diabetes. Years ago, when she took her blood sugar test, it usually went up to about 12 before dinner. A week before the city was shut down, she spent ten days in the hospital next to ours. The doctor gave him a prescription of Chinese medicine, she is now at home to take Chinese medicine, but the Chinese medicine is almost gone.

I just wish there was a way that we could go somewhere and see what's going on, see if the government is paying attention to these people. Even if you have to wait two or three months, at least there is a voice channel, let people feel at ease.

Now so many demands, but if no one care, we even every day in the micro-blog said it is no good.

■ Food available in the neighborhood where Vivian's parents live

Sy, reporter, interview for gastric cancer helpline

To be discharged from the hospital

On February 11,2020, I received a request for help from a family member who had been transferred by a friend. It read:

"advanced gastric cancer is a secondary recurrence. After 4 years of total gastrectomy, the bowel obstruction is severe. The patient is unable to swallow food and fluid. Its original admission to the Guangfa Group Tumor Hospital on the evening of February 5 by the superior temporary mandatory overall collection, all patients do not give an account, do not solve follow-up medical measures, immediately forced to leave home. Then and now, after a sudden cut off of external supplies and professional care, his physical condition has deteriorated dramatically and he is in critical condition. The patient himself is in great pain, and his family is distraught. Now urgent seeking, can be based on the above situation, can receive hospice care, or special period can provide home injection sedative analgesics! Only hope and time race, do your best to let the innocent life of the final dying process can be as humane as possible! "

After seeing the news, I helped the family ask some of my journalism colleagues, I also found some channels, 13, I decided to help him in the media appeal.

The patient was admitted to the care and attention department of the Guangfa Group Cancer Hospital on the evening of January 17. Because this kind of patient General Hospital does not accept, so later found this hospital, the condition is also better.

But on Feb. 3, the hospital was notified that one of the buildings might be used for fever patients, and that the old patients would move to a new building.

On the night of February 5th, around 6:00 p.m. , everyone was moving rooms. A doctor rushed out and said he had just been informed that all the patients with a fever would be admitted within two or three hours, so he had to move out immediately.

Such short notice indicates poor command and control. Because the above notice did not say when the deadline to move wards, so this time some patients have not started action. The hospital is very anxious, gather all the patients'relatives to the hospital, and move the ward quickly.

But what was even more dramatic was that around 7:50 p.m. , the head nurse suddenly received another phone call, and she was devastated. Originally, she received a superior notice, requiring all patients to leave the hospital within 10 to 20 minutes, because fever patients will soon arrive, the entire hospital has been confiscated.

Too busy to notice

Family members told me that the same batch of patients, including his family, there are about 15 people, only by infusion to maintain basic survival, rice water can not enter. In this case, suddenly let all patients leave the hospital immediately, in fact, is equivalent to the end of their lives.

The medics, too, were in a panic, unprepared and unprepared to take on a patient with a fever. Many relatives of patients in the hospital, said to complain. But under the so-called overall situation, to say the least, these people are indeed too busy to take care of, if not to say to be sacrificed

In the end, the patients were discharged. The family tried to contact the paramedics again, but the phones were disconnected.

The next morning, I received a friend's retweet, said that the patient went back after the deterioration of very severe, very painful.

There's a lot of things he says that make me sick. He says the patient can only howl, shaking the bed, like a child, the whole person left only instinct reaction, the body inflammation is recurring. No way to eat at all, as long as eat a little bit, will immediately double spit out, so the whole person quickly weak down.

At the time of my interview, I felt that the relatives were still actively contacting the hospital, whether it was Xiehe, Tongji, or 161 hospital. He contacted a hospital in Caidian District, but the hospital was outside the city, so he had to make a way out.

He went to the guy who made it, and the guy who made it told him to go to the neighborhood. The whole procedure is very cumbersome, layer by layer reporting, and so on government arrangements. But for a patient, every minute that goes by is a minute closer to death.

The next day, my friend informed me that the patient had died.

In fact, when I talked to my friends, I had a hunch that the patient might not last a few days. But he says a minute is a minute, at least a minute, of pain. It's basic humanity.

The family said there were about 15 patients in the same group. Are the remaining 14 people still alive, or are people dying every day? No one really knows.

For their families, it can take a long time to recover from their loss. But for the entire Wuhan Epidemic Prevention and control, they may not be included in any number.

The Internet uses the word "pneumonia secondary disaster" to describe this group, I think it is very appropriate. There are no statistics on how many of these people have died or are about to die. They could be a speck in history.

And then I wanted to write the patient's ending at the end of the script. I asked the family if they would like to say a few more words. He did not comment on the incident itself, but said: Thank you, and sincerely hope that your report can help more families and people.

Screenshot from a wechat chat between Siyi and her family

That one kind of stuck with me.

There's very little the media can do, but I want to be able to record as much as possible, and hope that these people are not at least buried in the dust of history.

——————

Cancer may not be as contagious as new coronary pneumonia, but people with cancer and new coronary pneumonia are all precious human beings. They all need help in the same way, and no one's treatment should be delayed.

It is hoped that the relevant departments will take remedial measures as soon as possible.

If you or your family have similar problems, feel free to leave a comment in the comments section, and we'll try to get more people to see you asking for help.
